<subSubSection id="C30A6528FFB1FF83C5BC1E51FBC0FC02" pageId="19" pageNumber="54" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BAF36A3FFB1FF83C5BC1E51FBC0FC02" blockId="19.[174,1127,574,903]" pageId="19" pageNumber="54">
Taxonomic notes. The Asiatic populations of 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D20FFB1FF83C6721E50FC3FFDDD" authorityName="Hufnagel" authorityYear="1766" box="[804,957,574,600]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Phalaena" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bombycina">
<emphasis id="B964EAB1FFB1FF83C6721E50FC3FFDDD" box="[804,957,574,600]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="54">P. bombycina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
clearly show a western-eastern subdivision with some overlap in 
<collectingCountry id="F3077633FFB1FF83C6611E30FC2DFDFC" box="[823,943,607,633]" name="Mongolia" pageId="19" pageNumber="54">Mongolia</collectingCountry>
. The west Asiatic group of populations has two contrasting forms (subspecies?) at the eastern edge of the range, (i) the dark bronze-brownish 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D20FFB1FF83C6641ECCFEE9FD5B" authority="Lehmann, 1998" authorityName="Lehmann" authorityYear="1998" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Polia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="54" phylum="Nemertea" rank="subSpecies" species="bombycina" subSpecies="puengeleri">
<emphasis id="B964EAB1FFB1FF83C6641ECCFBE5FD38" box="[818,1127,675,701]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="54">Polia bombycina puengeleri</emphasis>
Lehmann, 1998
</taxonomicName>
, described from [Kirghisia] Alexander Mts and occurring also in 
<collectingCountry id="F3077633FFB1FF83C59D1E89FEDEFC85" box="[203,348,742,768]" name="Kazakhstan" pageId="19" pageNumber="54">Kazakhstan</collectingCountry>
, and (ii) the pale fawn-coloured 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D20FFB1FF83C78B1E89FBAFFC85" authorityName="Varga" authorityYear="1974" box="[733,1069,742,768]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Polia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="54" phylum="Nemertea" rank="subSpecies" species="bombycina" subSpecies="psammochrea">
<emphasis id="B964EAB1FFB1FF83C78B1E89FBAFFC85" box="[733,1069,742,768]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="54">Polia bombycina psammochrea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Var- ga, 1974, described from 
<collectingCountry id="F3077633FFB1FF83C48B1F68FDD7FCA4" box="[477,597,775,801]" name="Mongolia" pageId="19" pageNumber="54">Mongolia</collectingCountry>
, Govi Altai aimak, Khasaght Khajrhan Mts. The taxonomic subdivision of the eastern group (cf. 
<taxonomicName id="4C104D20FFB1FF83C6731F46FEA7FCE0" authority="(Butler, 1878))" baseAuthorityName="Butler" baseAuthorityYear="1878" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Polia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="54" phylum="Nemertea" rank="subSpecies" species="bombycina" subSpecies="grisea">
<emphasis id="B964EAB1FFB1FF83C6731F46FBA1FCC6" box="[805,1059,809,835]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="54">Polia bombycina grisea</emphasis>
(Butler, 1878))
</taxonomicName>
described under some different names (see: 
<bibRefCitation id="EF814B52FFB1FF83C6121F24FB93FCE0" author="VARGA, Z. &amp; RONKAY, G. &amp; RONKAY, L." box="[836,1041,843,869]" pageId="19" pageNumber="54" pagination="133 - 160" refId="ref12050" refString="VARGA, Z., RONKAY, G. &amp; RONKAY, L. (2017): Revised taxonomic check list of the Eurasiatic species of the subtribe Poliina (Noctuidae, Noctuinae, Hadenini). - Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift 64 (2): 133 - 160. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / dez. 64.21455" type="journal article" year="2017">
VARGA 
<emphasis id="B964EAB1FFB1FF83C6CD1F23FC50FCE0" box="[923,978,843,869]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="54">et al.</emphasis>
2017
</bibRefCitation>
) needs further surveys, as well as the populations occurring in the Caucasus range.
</paragraph>
